We must “derive” the gross profit from the sales transactions. For every transaction of type “Sale” we take the given “profit” value and add them all together. In our data the “Sale” rows (those with type “Sale”) are the ones with an already‐calculated profit (the last column). (Other types – “Purchase”, “Expense”, etc. – do not contribute to gross profit.)

2. We then sum these profit numbers step‐by‐step:

 – For the first five “Sale” rows:  
  2808.37 + 10304.98 + 61696.18 + 14973.05 + 3923.61 = 93,706.19

 – Next five (rows 6–10):  
  30506.16 + 3339.15 + 4362.40 + 82514.73 + 135393.08 = 256,115.52  
  Subtotal so far: 93,706.19 + 256,115.52 = 349,821.71

 – Next five (rows 11–15):  
  39573.99 + 55008.10 + 11511.56 + 54821.85 + 31954.68 = 192,870.18  
  Subtotal: 349,821.71 + 192,870.18 = 542,691.89

 – Next five (rows 16–20):  
  171035.10 + 3604.58 + 7511.16 + 11289.99 + 7234.06 = 200,674.89  
  Subtotal: 542,691.89 + 200,674.89 = 743,366.78

 – Next five (rows 21–25):  
  48859.80 + 148623.60 + 8125.11 + 10199.88 + 18078.00 = 233,886.39  
  Subtotal: 743,366.78 + 233,886.39 = 977,253.17

 – Next five (rows 26–30):  
  3128.95 + 114316.17 + 15902.30 + 69306.76 + 12567.84 = 215,222.02  
  Subtotal: 977,253.17 + 215,222.02 = 1,192,475.19

 – Next five (rows 31–35):  
  185524.45 + 43734.24 + 1013.22 + 23035.77 + 10224.21 = 263,531.89  
  Subtotal: 1,192,475.19 + 263,531.89 = 1,456,007.08

 – Final four rows (rows 36–39):  
  25539.92 + 78373.95 + 28279.10 + 14300.25 = 146,493.22  
  Grand total: 1,456,007.08 + 146,493.22 = 1,602,500.30

3. Thus, the sum of all the sales “profit” values is 1,602,500.30.

This total represents the gross profit item in the income statement (sales revenue less cost of goods sold as represented by the “profit” on each sale).
